{{Other uses|David Clarke (disambiguation){{!}}David Clarke}}

'''David Clarke''' is the founder and Chairman of the [[Australia]]n online travel agent [[Webjet]] Limited, listed as [[Australian Securities Exchange|ASX]]: [http://www.asx.com.au/asx/research/companyInfo.do?by=asxCode&asxCode=WEB WEB]. 

Clarke started Webjet as a hobby after he semi-retired at the age of 50.  When the company floated on the [[Australian Securities Exchange]] in 1999, Webjet was valued at {{AUD}}4 million. In 2008 Webjet recorded A$350 million in [[revenue]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.australianit.news.com.au/story/0,,23131190-15318,00.html?from=public_rss |title=Webjet chief's relief at missing out on Travel.com |work=The Australian |date=20 January 2008 |accessdate=4 May 2012 |author=Odi, Teresa }}</ref>

