{{Orphan|date=May 2017}} {{Infobox magazine | title = Affärsmagasinet Forum | image_file = | image_size = | image_caption = | editor = Torsten Fagerholm<ref name="yle">{{cite web|title=Fagerholm ska leda affärsmagasinet Forum|url=https://svenska.yle.fi/artikel/2013/07/01/fagerholm-ska-leda-affarsmagasinet-forum|publisher=[[Yle]]|accessdate=6 June 2017}}</ref>
| editor_title = Editor in Chief | founder = Amos Anderson | frequency = Monthly | category = Business magazine | company = | publisher = | founded = 1968 | firstdate = | finaldate = | based = [[Helsingfors]] | country = [[Finland]] | circulation = 10 944 (print)<ref name="tidskrift">{{cite web|url=http://forum.tidskrift.fi/start/ |title=Forum för ekonomi och teknik|publisher=tidskrift.fi |accessdate=6 June 2017}}</ref> | language = [[Swedish language|Swedish]] | website = http://www.forummag.fi/ | issn = 0533-070X | oclc = }}
'''''Forum''''' business magazine (''Affärsmagasinet Forum'', ''Forum för ekonomi och teknik'') is a monthly magazine published in print and online. It is Finland's only Swedish-language business, technology and management publication.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.forummag.fi/information-in-english/ |title=Information in english - Forum |website=Forummag.fi |date=2011-11-14 |accessdate=2017-05-29}}</ref>
Forum focuses on how emerging technologies affect the economy and society from a career and management perspective. Coverage areas include entrepreneurship and innovations in [[Finland]] and the Nordic area, as well as the Baltics, the US and Asia. The magazine reaches 27,000 well-educated readers<ref name="tidskrift"/> in management positions, mainly business graduates, engineers and architects, both in Finland and abroad.
Roughly 76% of readers work in management positions or as entrepreneurs.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.forummag.fi/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Forum_mediekort_2017_NY.pdf |format=PDF |title=Forum |date=2017 |website=Forummag.fi |accessdate=2017-05-29}}</ref>
==History and profile== Forum’s was founded in 1968 through a merger of various technology and business publications whose roots stretch back to 1880. Forum’s stated mission is to act as an ”independent liberal magazine, editorially free from any party or organization, striving to promote a spirit of humanistic enlightenment, democracy, open and transparent business, as well as innovation and entrepreneurship”.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.forummag.fi/information-om-forum/ |title=Information om tidskriften - Forum |website=Forummag.fi |date=2011-11-14 |accessdate=2017-05-29}}</ref> [[Torsten Fagerholm]] is editor-in-chief since 2013.<ref name="yle"/> His predecessors include [[Patrik Lindfors]],<ref>{{cite web|title="Patrik Lindfors ny kommunikationschef för Centralhandelskammaren"|url=https://svenska.yle.fi/artikel/2013/04/30/patrik-lindfors-ny-kommunikationschef-centralhandelskammaren|publisher=[[Yle]]|accessdate=6 June 2017}}</ref> [[Fredrik Nars]] and [[Ragnhild Artimo]].
