{{refimprove|date=April 2012}} {{infobox university |name = Lahore School of Economics |image = Lahore School of Economics (emblem).jpg |image_size = 120px |undergrad = 2200 |established = 1993 |type = [[Private school|Private]] |head_label = Rector |head = [[Dr. Shahid Amjad Chaudhary]] |city = [[Lahore]] |state = [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]] |country = [[Pakistan]] |campus = [[Urban area|Urban]], 50 acres |website = {{URL|www.lahoreschoolofeconomics.edu.pk}} }}
The '''Lahore School of Economics (LSE)''' is an [[Private university|independent]] [[Research university|research]] university based in [[Lahore]], [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]] established in 1993 and chartered by the [[Government of Punjab, Pakistan|government]] in January 1997. It has currently 200 faculty members and over 3,000 students studying undergraduate, graduate and post-graduate programs.<ref>[http://tribune.com.pk/story/523911/management-conference-at-lahore-school-of-economics/ Management conference at Lahore School of Economics]</ref><ref name="Address of LSE">{{cite web|last=Google maps|title=Address of LSE|url=https://maps.google.com/maps?ie=UTF8&q=lahore+school+of+economics&fb=1&hq=lahore+school+of+economics&cid=11155377561400795393&hnear=&ll=31.502568,74.474902&spn=0.011142,0.021136&t=m&z=16&vpsrc=0&iwloc=A|publisher=Google maps|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>
The Lahore School was founded by Dr. Shahid Amjad Chaudhry, a [[McGill University|McGill]] trained economist, who served as the deputy chair of the influential [[Planning Commission (Pakistan)|Planning Commission]]. The Lahore School has two campuses: the Main campus and the City campus. The Main campus, spread over {{convert|50|acre|m2}} and the city campus is located in [[Gulberg Liberty, Lahore|Gulberg]]. Its faculty comprise over 150 permanent faculty members with specialisations in Economics, Business Administration, Social Sciences, Mathematics & Statistics, Environmental Studies, Media Studies, Art and Design.<ref>[http://www.lahoreschoolofeconomics.edu.pk/Faculty/Faculty.aspx Lahore School of Economics faculty]</ref>
The Lahore School consists of two distinctive institutes, including the Graduate Institute of Development Studies which carries out research and training in [[international development]], the Centre for Research in Economics and Business, which publishes the Lahore Journal of Economics and the Lahore Journal of Business.<ref>[http://www.lahoreschoolofeconomics.edu.pk/Businessjournal/Lahorejournalofbusiness.aspx Lahore Journal of Business]</ref>
LSE is regarded as one of the more notable private research institutions of higher learning in Pakistan and since 2015 its business school is consistently ranked the 2nd best business school in Pakistan according to the [[Higher Education Commission (Pakistan)|Higher Education Commission]].<ref>[http://www.hec.gov.pk/InsideHEC/Divisions/QALI/Others/RankingofUniversities/Pages/CategoryWise.aspx HEC Rankings] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525073744/http://www.hec.gov.pk/InsideHEC/Divisions/QALI/Others/RankingofUniversities/Pages/CategoryWise.aspx |date=2013-05-25 }}</ref><ref>[http://tribune.com.pk/story/523911/management-conference-at-lahore-school-of-economics/ Management conference at Lahore School of Economics]</ref>
